  "prompt": "How do I install and configure PCSX2 for a Raspberry Pi 3 running RetroPie 3.6 updated to the lates version?",
  "response": "Here's a step-by-step guide to install PCSX2 on RetroPie for Raspberry Pi 3:\n\n1. SSH into your Raspberry Pi or use terminal\n\n2. Update your system:\n```\nsudo apt-get update\nsudo apt-get upgrade\n```\n\n3. Install required dependencies:\n```\nsudo apt-get install cmake git libpcsx2-dev libwxgtk3.0-dev libgtk-3-dev\n```\n\n4. Install additional dependencies:\n```\nsudo apt-get install libsdl2-dev libportaudio2 libportaudiocpp0\n```\n\n5. Clone PCSX2 repository:\n```\ncd ~\ngit clone https://github.com/PCSX2/pcsx2.git\ncd pcsx2\n```\n\n6. Create build directory:\n```\nmkdir build\ncd build\n```\n\n7. Configure and compile:\n```\ncmake ..\nmake\nsudo make install\n```\n\n8. Configure BIOS (requires legal PS2 BIOS dump)\n- Place BIOS files in `~/.config/PCSX2/bios/`\n\n9. Add to RetroPie:\n- Edit `~/RetroPie-Setup/platforms.cfg`\n- Add PS2 emulator configuration\n\nNote: Performance might be limited on Raspberry Pi 3. Full-speed PS2 emulation is challenging on this hardware.\n\nRecommended alternative: Consider using alternative PS2 emulators like PPSSPP for better performance.",
